{
  "version": 1,
  "description": "B8 adversarial PII recall corpus. Measures the RECALL of this library itself (scrub / containsPii / scrubSemantic) on PII hidden in the shapes real repos and activity streams produce. DISTINCT from the B7 TS<->Python parity corpus at career-box-dev/evals/redaction-parity/ (75 fixtures, cross-language agreement) — that corpus asks 'do both implementations agree', this one asks 'does the library catch it at all'. Consumed by test/recall-gate.test.ts, which ratchets per-category recall against eval/recall-baseline.json. Fixtures with expected='miss' are xfail-style documentation of current gaps: the gate asserts they STILL miss, so a pattern fix flips them visibly (promote to 'caught' + regenerate the baseline). NEVER delete or weaken a fixture to make the suite pass; NEVER silently skip a gap — document it. Pattern fixes are follow-up PRs gated by this corpus.",
  "modes": {
    "scrub": "caught iff no planted value (nor mustNotSurvive fragment) survives in scrub(input).redacted at default (low) threshold",
    "detect": "caught iff containsPii(input, { minSeverity: 'high' }) is true — for detectOnly patterns that escalate sensitivity but never rewrite text",
    "semantic": "caught iff no planted term survives in scrubSemantic(input).redacted"
  },
